==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metropolis
<hw>Me*trop"o*lis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>metropolis</ets>, Gr. <?/, prop., the mother city (in relation to
colonies); <?/ mother + <?/ city. See <er>Mother</er>, and
<er>Police</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The mother city; the chief city of a kingdom, state,
or country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Edinburgh] gray <qex>metropolis</qex> of the North.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The seat, or see, of the
metropolitan, or highest church dignitary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The great <qex>metropolis</qex> and see of Rome.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Any large city.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metropolitan</ent>⟦br⟧
